<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The dollar was lower in thin early European trading today and foreign currency dealers said they do n't expect it to break out of a narrow trading range before new American trade figures are released next week. Gold prices were mixed. The January trade report is due to be released March 17 and one dealer at a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> bank in <LOCATION> Frankfurt </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION>, said the market will be paralyzed until then. `` We just move along from trade figure to trade figure,'' he said. In <LOCATION> Tokyo </LOCATION>, where trading ends as <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION>'s business day begins, the dollar fell 0.35 yen to a closing 128.87. Later, in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, it was quoted at 128.60 yen. Other dollar rates at midmorning, compared with late Friday: _ 1.6865 West German marks, down from 1.6940 _ 1.3960 Swiss francs, down from 1.4030 _ 5.7090 French francs, down from 5.7300 _ 1.8952 Dutch guilders, down from 1.9010 _ 1,243.75 Italian lire, down from 1,248.00 _ 1.2535 Canadian dollars, down from 1.2547 In <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>, one British pound cost $ 1.7972, more expensive than Traders said the pound was strong throughout <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> because of relatively high British interest rates. Gold prices were lower in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> and higher in <LOCATION> Zurich </LOCATION>. The metal opened in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> at a bid price of $ 437 a troy ounce, compared with late Friday's $ 437.50. At midmorning today, the city's five major bullion dealers fixed a recommended price of $ 436. One bullion dealer said market participants in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> were taking profits following Friday's technical rally in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. `` It is going to keep falling,'' he said. `` There is a lot of selling around.'' In <LOCATION> Zurich </LOCATION>, the bid price was $ 434.25, up from $ 432 late Friday. Earlier, in <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION>, gold rose 54 cents to close at a bid $ 438.75. Silver was quoted in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> today at a bid price of $ 6.38 a troy ounce, down from Friday's $ 6.41.
