<HEAD>Student Says Youths Laughed As They Watched Her Being Raped</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSON, Miss. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A special education student says no other youths moved to help her when two boys raped her in a classroom, and when the bell rang at the end of the period they left laughing. The Magee resident also said two boys charged with the rape at <ORGANIZATION> Magee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> had harassed her for about two years. `` Me and -LRB- he -RRB- fight every day,'' the 16-year-old girl said in a weekend interview with The Clarion Ledger at her parents' rural <LOCATION> Simpson </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> home. `` He just picks on me and call my mom and daddy names.'' The girl said she was raped by two male students on Feb. 26 while she and other students were in study hall under the supervision of teacher <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Grantham </PERSON>, who said he had gone to check on a school bus he drives when the attack occurred. The girl, who has a learning disability, and her family agreed to discuss the attack if their identities were n't disclosed, the newspaper said Sunday. The girl said the youths, ages 15 and 17, grabbed her around the neck when she and another girl went to sharpen their pencils. They grabbed the other girl, too, but let her go, she said. `` They carried me in the back of the room. I told them to leave me alone.'' The girl said the youths pulled off her underwear, and each raped her twice, she said. `` One was holding me,'' she said. `` Every time I tried to get up, they hold me down.'' The attack occurred within sight of several other students, she said. All the students in the study hall, except for one of the attackers, were regular students, said <PERSON> Betty </PERSON> <PERSON> Dickson </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Simpson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> School </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> chairwoman. One of the boys is educably mentally retarded, according to special education director <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Hardy </PERSON>. No one stopped the attack, the girl said, even though she told the other girl at the pencil sharpener to alert a principal or teacher. `` When the bell rang, they walked out the door, laughing,'' she said. The girl's father said he is as upset with school officials as he is the two boys. `` I send them to learn, not to be going down there to get raped,'' he said. The father said he called police and took his daughter to <ORGANIZATION> Magee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hospital </ORGANIZATION> that night to be examined. The two youths were arrested Thursday, charged with rape and jailed in lieu of $ 50,000 bond each. Although they will be tried as adults, officials refused to release their names. <PERSON> Dickson </PERSON> said school officials are planning counseling for the girl.
