<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The widow of former <ORGANIZATION> CIA </ORGANIZATION> director <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Casey </PERSON> testified today before the special federal grand jury that is investigating the Iran-Contra affair. <PERSON> Sophia </PERSON> <PERSON> Casey </PERSON> likely was questioned about what her husband might have told her before his death last year about the sale of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> arms to <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> to obtain the release of American hostages and whether he mentioned anything about the diversion of proceeds to the Contras. <PERSON> Casey </PERSON>, who died of pneumonia on May 6, 1987, after suffering from brain cancer, was <ORGANIZATION> CIA </ORGANIZATION> director when <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> arm were sold to <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> in 1985 and 1986. The agency provided logistical support to covert operations to help the Contras. Those operations were coordinated by former <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Security </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Council </ORGANIZATION> aide Lt. Col. <PERSON> Oliver </PERSON> <PERSON> L. </PERSON> <PERSON> North </PERSON>. <PERSON> North </PERSON> told <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> that he was acting with <PERSON> Casey </PERSON>'s approval and that the former <ORGANIZATION> CIA </ORGANIZATION> director recommended that he recruit retired <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> Maj. Gen. <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> V. </PERSON> <PERSON> Secord </PERSON> to set up the private supply network because <PERSON> Secord </PERSON> had experience in special operations. <PERSON> Secord </PERSON>, who set up secret Swiss bank accounts to funnel private donations to the Contras, also helped broker the sale of <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> arms to <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> with his partner, <PERSON> Albert </PERSON> <PERSON> Hakim </PERSON>. <PERSON> North </PERSON> told <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATI